On Mon, Dec 14, 2009 at 9:44 PM, Gordon Mohr &lt;gojomo@...&gt; wrote:

&gt; anas elghafari wrote:
&gt; &gt; I am running Heritrix 1.14.3 and JVM 1.6. Anyway, thank you for the tip,
&gt; &gt; I found where the problem is: Basically Writer processor that I wrote as
&gt; &gt; a test goes into an infinite loop with 0.01 probability (I wrote that to
&gt; &gt; test the effects of a writer  that tries talking to an Indexer that has
&gt; &gt; crashed).
&gt;
&gt; Happy to hear you found the problem.
&gt;
&gt; &gt; It would be nice is to be able to pause the crawl job from within a
&gt; &gt; Writer. CrawlJobHandler has the pauseJob() method. Is there a way for a
&gt; &gt; processor to access the CrawlJobHandler?
&gt;
&gt; Take a look at the LowDiskPauseProcessor for an example -- modules
&gt; inside &quot;the crawl&quot; should send such requests through the
&gt; CrawlController. (The CrawlJobHandler is an operator-UI-related class
&gt; that shouldn&#39;t be of interest to crawl implementation classes.)
&gt;
&gt; Hope this helps,
&gt;
&gt; - Gordon @ IA
